        "content": "<p>Is there some nice way in Lean to say \"Precisely one of these statements holds\"?</p>\n<p>For example, suppose I want to say that \"precisely one of a &lt; b, a = b, a &gt; b holds\".  I could write</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">∨</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">∨</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">∧</span> <span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">∧</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">∧</span> <span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">∧</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">∧</span> <span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">∧</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but it seems unduly repetitive.  Is there a nicer way?</p>",
